It is worth noting that the capital Malabo before 1968 was a Spanish city, and the native population learned to practice the lands of Equatorial Guinea with the Spaniards cultural tradition.

Natural Phenomenon

The climate of this country is tropical where flora and fauna are distributed throughout the year. Some researchers say that the stars of Johanna Mountains and highlands are a sightseeing place on the planet for all devotees of astronomical research.

Museum

A trip to Central Africa is accompanied by French art exhibitions at the Hidnoz Art Gallery. It should be noted that the museum occupies a central position among the four corners of this city that houses rare African art. Do not miss this interesting destination for the collection of 300 sculptures and wooden masks from the colonial era until today.

Archaeological Museum

As in most tribes of the jungle, this place hosts a set of objects, classical paintings and ethnography, in addition to ancient stones and jewels. For example, some carvings relate to myths that have been known in the national culture for centuries. Another collection refers to rituals, religious practices, and traditions that remain intact despite the passage of years.
